content: I really like the Kate Spade Cameron Street Tote, but it's a bit pricey. I've been using my backpack for daily commute, and it's been great for carrying my laptop, water bottle, and other essentials. Speaking of which, I remember I bought that backpack on January 15th at the outdoor gear store downtown, and it's been a great investment. Anyway, back to the tote, do you think there are any more affordable options that still have multiple compartments and can fit my laptop and water bottle?
